From: Arnaldo Carvalho de Melo <acme@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jan 2025 15:05:56 -0300
Subject: perf config: Add a function to set one variable in .perfconfig
Git-commit: e9cbc854d8b148e3491291fb615e94261970fb54
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

To allow for setting a variable from some other tool, like with the
"wallclock" patchset needs to allow the user to opt-in to having
that key in the sort order for 'perf report'.

